\par \plain\f3\fs20     This simple formula is a best description of the \plain\f3\fs20\b "Skingine" \plain\f3\fs20 word . Skinganes are programming engines for working with skins. Skingine is a component that incapsulates a collection of hot areas ({\uldb regions}{\v Regions>Main}) and allows apply different skins on a fly. The hot area behaviour is not depended on the skin. Only the shape and position of the hot area are specified by the skin. Hot area ({\uldb region}{\v Regions>Main}) is a something like an usual control, it has properties and events, but doesn't have a static position and size. Skingine fully controls drawing, painting and mouse routines. Also skingine controls the shape of the parenent form, this feature allows create non-rectangual forms and user intrfaces.
\par 
\par The \plain\f4\fs20 {\uldb krpRegion library}{\v Overview>Main} contains two different skingines: 
\par 
\par \pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\plain\f4\fs20 1. {\uldb TkrpRectSkingine}{\v TkrpRectSkingine} - skingine with one shape region (generated from \plain\f4\fs20\b mask\plain\f4\fs20  by \plain\f4\fs20\b color key\plain\f4\fs20 ) for the parent form and many rectangular hot areas (declared by coordinates of rectangles). 
\par 2. {\uldb TkrpColorSkingine}{\v TkrpColorSkingine} - skingine is a realization of the {\uldb AREA_BY_COLOR}{\v AREA_BY_COLOR>Main} algorithm, supports many hot non-rectangular areas (given from \plain\f4\fs20\b multi-color mask\plain\f4\fs20  by \plain\f4\fs20\b color keys\plain\f4\fs20 ). 
